window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Magnus leaves. He fights. He tries to survive.</b></p> <p><i>“Can you tell me what happened tae her, how she ended?” (Magnus in 2381)</i></p> <p>Magnus is forced to travel to an uncertain future, to fight for a throne he doesn't want. And he couldn't bring Kaitlyn because it's too dangerous by far.</p> <p>So, Kaitlyn tries to live on without him. She's 263 years in the past now. Nothing but dust. But there's a time travel vessel that's been lost. And a warrior who needs to be rescued.</p> <p>And sometimes, a history that 100 percent happened can still be changed. Because it's not too late.</p> <p><i>“I don’t want any help. I just want Magnus to come home.” (Kaitlyn in 2018)</i></p> <p><b>Excerpt from the book:</b></p> <p>I clutched harder, his fingers wet with my tears. “I don’t know if I can bear it.”</p> <p>He breathed out like a sigh. “If ye are nae strong enough, what will happen tae us?”</p> <p>“I don’t know...”</p> <p>He wriggled his fingers from my grasp and wiped the tears from my cheek. “Then ye need tae be strong enough, mo reul-iuil. We are countin’ on ye...”</p>"; 
